hands_on_practices.solution:
The retroactivity load for a device is defined as the fractional decrease in reference RFP fluorescence upon induction, given by
$$
L_{R}=\frac{F_{\text{RFP, OFF}}-F_{\text{RFP, ON}}}{F_{\text{RFP, OFF}}}.
$$
For Device A,
$$
L_{R,A}=\frac{F_{\text{RFP, A, OFF}}-F_{\text{RFP, A, ON}}}{F_{\text{RFP, A, OFF}}}
=\frac{12{,}580-10{,}990}{12{,}580}
=\frac{1{,}590}{12{,}580}
=\frac{159}{1{,}258}\approx 0.126391.
$$
For Device B,
$$
L_{R,B}=\frac{F_{\text{RFP, B, OFF}}-F_{\text{RFP, B, ON}}}{F_{\text{RFP, B, OFF}}}
=\frac{12{,}610-9{,}331}{12{,}610}
=\frac{3{,}279}{12{,}610}\approx 0.260032.
$$
The requested ratio is
$$
\frac{L_{R,B}}{L_{R,A}}=\frac{\frac{3{,}279}{12{,}610}}{\frac{1{,}590}{12{,}580}}
=\frac{3{,}279\cdot 12{,}580}{12{,}610\cdot 1{,}590}
=\frac{3{,}279\cdot 1{,}258}{12{,}610\cdot 159}
=\frac{1093\cdot 629}{53\cdot 6305}
=\frac{687{,}497}{334{,}165}\approx 2.05736.
$$
Rounding to three significant figures gives $2.06$.
